  "local_patches": [
    "grammar/cel.lark: BYTES_LIT/STRING_LIT/MLSTRING_LIT quantifier typo {4-8} -> {4,8} (2 sites). Upstream writes \\u[0-9a-fA-F]{4-8}; backtracking engines silently demote the malformed quantifier to literal text (a LITERAL {4-8} in Python re), so the patch is a genuine language change, not a no-op. Patched in the vendored copy (we do not file upstream bugs); verified at patch time by byte-identical oracle regeneration — no vendored input exercises the literal-{4-8} reading.",
    "REFRESH WARNING: the oracle generator parses this PATCHED grammar, so the byte-identical check above was a one-time verification. If cel inputs are ever refreshed, RE-VERIFY: temporarily revert the patch, regenerate the cel oracle, and diff — a new input hitting the literal-{4-8} reading would otherwise freeze a non-upstream oracle silently (lark-rs would agree with it and the freshness gate would stay green)."
  ]
